messages.messageBody:
Brenda,
Oh, I will. ;-) I still feel bad about not being able to meet you.
Migraines are the pits! I wish I got it before or _after_ you left.
Well...not at all really. LOL!
We're coming in thursday evening. Kelly, can I help you and Brenda with
anything that night? I just *know* your nerves will be fried. <BWWG> Buy you
a drink?


Barb E
"Children have more need of models than of critics."

- Carolyn Coats, Author




> Glad to hear they like them. I've been saving up for the conference; I have
> lots of non-German euros now! You'll have to come take a peek.
>
> I'll see you in SC, with quarters. Thanks much. I'm glad that I'll finally
> get to meet you, since Columbus never happened!
>
> brenda

>
> Christina,
>
> We should be able to pretty easily split the coins up between anyone who's
> interested. There's a LOT of coins, and many, many of them are duplicates.
> I'll sort you out some before I leave, if I have time.
>
> I'll be easy to find -- I'll be the one Kelly is running around like her
> personal conference-slave! (I'm coming in early and hanging around in S.C.
> for two weeks beforehand to see old friends, new friends, and hopefully be
> reasonably useful to Kelly.)
>
> We'll find each other. Promise!
>
> brenda
